          <div class="timeline-content reveal delay-1">
            <h3>Establishment of the First Business</h3>
            <p>Sheikh Hamad founded Hamad Algosaibi Co. in the Eastern Province. During this decade, he built strong ties with Saudi Aramco, supplying silver coins for employee salaries and supporting the company&rsquo;s early operational needs. He also played a key role in supporting the establishment of the Eastern Province Chamber of Commerce in collaboration with Prince Saud bin Jalawi.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item tl-year-right">
          <div class="timeline-content reveal">
            <h3>Expansion and Diversification</h3>
            <p>The company witnessed significant growth, expanding into logistics, industrial supply, and automotive sectors. It became a distributor for Ford Motor Company and an agent for Esso. During this period, Sheikh Hamad also established the first Pepsi Cola bottling plant in the Eastern Province, marking a major milestone in the region&rsquo;s industrial development.</p>
          </div>
